# Conquest Design Law

Conquest UI is governed by **UXMD Volumes I–III** and **GIS** — not archived pre-UXMD design docs.

Read before any UI work:

- `docs/uxmd/volume-i-user-experience-master-document.md`
- `docs/uxmd/volume-ii-screen-interaction-specification.md`
- `docs/uxmd/volume-iii-global-interaction-standards.md`

**Build is not authorized.** `apps/gateway/public/preview.*` is a pipeline demo only — not the UXMD application.

## Principles (from UXMD)

- Command Center is home (ADR-0002)
- Seven-item primary navigation (ADR-0005)
- Workspace is context, not nav (ADR-0003)
- GIS inheritance on all screens unless documented override (ADR-0012)

## Forbidden

- Generic sidebar + cards + charts layout substituting for UXMD screens
- Intelligence machinery as navigation items
- Implementation without GIS accessibility gate (ENG-23)
